<li id="cite_note-stephan-2">^ <a href="#cite_ref-stephan_2-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-stephan_2-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> John J. Stephan, <i>The Russian Far East: A History</i>. Published by Stanford University Press, 1996. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0804727015" class="internal">ISBN 0804727015</a> <a href="http://books.google.com.au/books?id=Jce4rBWjG5wC" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com.au/books?id=Jce4rBWjG5wC" rel="nofollow">Partial text</a> on Google Books. pp. 18-19, 51.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> "Siberia Today and Tomorrow: A Study of Economic Resources, Problems, and Achievements", By Violet Conolly. Published by Collins, 1975. <a href="http://books.google.com.au/books?id=osW5AAAAIAA" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com.au/books?id=osW5AAAAIAA" rel="nofollow">Snippet view only</a> on Google Books.</li>
